description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for a dedicated Place of Safety Team in Canterbury. This is an exciting and brand new opportunity for staff who enjoy the challenge of working in an acute front line mental health service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for caring and highly motivated health care worker who can demonstrate an enthusiastic approach to working with people who have been detained on a Section 136 of the Mental Health Act and require admission to the Place of Safety. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will need to demonstrate a positive and proactive approach in meeting the individual nursing care needs of detained persons in the suite which will encompass safety and risk management.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant would benefit of having a good understanding of Section 136 of the Mental Health Act &amp; complex needs mental health needs; such as dual diagnosis.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition successful applicant will require excellent communication and de- escalation skills and will be required to successfully complete PSS training. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return we offer the successful applicant the opportunity to work as part of dedicated team and will support continued personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kerri Scutts - 07557 596 975&lt;/p&gt;
